# UI Floating Avatar Effects

## Context
Adding rich, interactive floating avatar effects to enhance the user experience and create a more dynamic, engaging interface. This work transforms static floating cursors and avatars into interactive entities with physics, visual flair, and off-screen discoverability.

## Goal
- Implement particle effects around floating avatars
- Add avatar animations (size animating, spinning, poking)
- Implement collision detection and "bounce away" physics for multiple avatars
- Create glowing effects and colorful animating borders (color, intensity, size)
- Implement scroll correction to bring avatars into view when scrolled out of sight or indicate their off-screen presence

## Non-Goals
- Complete redesign of the underlying presence or websocket system
- Creating new backend API routes unless strictly needed for synchronizing effects
- Full physics engine implementation beyond simple 2D collision/bouncing for avatars

## Steps
1. Design and implement the base animation system for size, spinning, and poking (interactions).
2. Implement glowing effects and dynamic border animations (CSS/framer-motion).
3. Develop particle effects around the floating avatar.
4. Implement physics for collision detection and bouncing between multiple floating avatars.
5. Implement scroll correction logic to ensure avatars remain visible or discoverable when scrolling.

## Verification
- Run frontend checks to ensure animations perform smoothly without lag.
- Test collision physics with multiple simulated user avatars on screen.
- Verify scroll correction accurately tracks and reveals off-screen avatars without jank.
- Validate that visual effects do not interfere with page clickability or text selection.

